The Yerry Mina saga has taken another twist with Wolves now showing interest in the Barcelona defender,National Daily gathered.
The Colombia international, who impressed during their World Cup campaign, was not included in Barcelona’s squad for their US pre-season tour.
Everton, Manchester United and Lyon have all been credited with interest, but
Tuttomercatoweb claim another two Premier League clubs are in contention.
They claim Wolves have offered £13million plus a further £4m in performance-related add-ons.
However, the report continues to state that Mina is stalling on his future because he wants to join Unai Emery at Arsenal.
